OL,5,EA THOUGHT:                S/--&Q+'S.+.+
OL,6,E                                       
OL,7,BThe legend of King Arthur says he's    
OL,8,Basleep in Avalon, waiting until Britain
OL,9,Bneeds him once more.                   
OL,11,BIt also tells of how, as high King, he 
OL,12,Blearned he had a duty to preserve the  
OL,13,Bsanctity of the land. Not only the     
OL,14,Bphysical andBspiritual landscape, but  
OL,15,Bits peopleB- no matter what their      
OL,16,Bcolour, creedBor status. Is it notBtime
OL,17,Bwe awakenedBthe Arthur in us all?  E   
OL,18,EPagan Andy, believing in the Old GodsB 
OL,19,BPS Fiar Bitchy Witchy, you flatter me! 
OL,20,G``````````````````````````````````2/5``
OL,21,C Such chivalry went out with stoning.  
OL,22,A]MGBRING IT BACK? PULL THEFUTHERGONE!  
